Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: knihy, fyzické nebo digitální, kde si čtenář může vybrat z možností, jak změnit konec příběhu; pokud je to možné, použijte s dalším kódem YF*, který označuje žánr, i po tomto kódu

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Thrillery
Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Detektivky & tajemné příběhy
Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Vojenská & válečná beletrie
Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Horory & strašidelné příběhy, drsné příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: any story that features ghosts, or is a supernatural scary story. Use with: YNX* codes for stories about specific supernatural or paranormal beings Zobrazit také YNXW

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Spekulativní beletrie, dystopie & utopie
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: beletrie odehrávající se v dystopické nebo utopické společnosti, alternativní historická beletrie; použijte společně s YFG nebo dalšími kódy YF*, pokud je to možné

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Apocalyptic and post-apocalyptic stories
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: end of the world stories, dying earth, collapsing or collapsed civilizations. Use for: stories set in worlds trying to prevent, or experiencing or that have already been affected by an apocalypse event, such as runaway climate change, an impact event, resource depletion, nuclear holocaust, pandemics, end times, zombie apocalypse, cybernetic revolts, technological singularity, invasion from space, dysgenics, etc
Use for: stories for children or teenagers with a superhero character or where the main characters are depicted as superheroes

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Science fiction
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: YNTT for Time travel, time slip, or time loop sci-fi stories, YNXF for stories about extra-terrestrials or UFOs, YNNZ for stories about space travel, YNTC for stories about AI, Mecha, robots or new technology, etc

Class here: Galactic empires, interstellar or intergalactic wars. Use for: science fiction stories set in space, in imagined galaxies or universes, or on different planets, often with advanced cultures and sophisticated technology and usually featuring main characters who are children or teenagers

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Steampunk (podžánr sci-fi nebo fantasy)
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: dieselpunk, cyberpunk, retrofuturism. Use for: science fiction based on an alternative world where, for example in the case of steampunk, 19th century steam power has emerged as the dominant technology

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Fantasy & magický realismus
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: paranormal fantasy, enchanted journeys, alternative worlds, accidental travel, portal fantasy, Isekai. Use all YFH* codes with: YNX* codes as appropriate, with YNXB* codes for stories featuring the paranormal or particular supernatural beings

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Epic fantasy / heroic fantasy
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: sword and sorcery fantasy, quest fantasy, high fantasy

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Magical realism / Magical fantasy
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: Magical girl. Use for: works that incorporates fantastic, magical, mythical or supernatural elements into an otherwise real-world or mundane setting, or works where the magic itself – whether a magical object or a character with magical powers – is the subject of the story, rather than simply a means to an end. Use with: YNXW for stories about witches, wizards or magicians or YNXB* codes for other magical creatures

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Mythic fantasy / Mythic fiction
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: Fairy tale retellings, fractured fairy tales, Arthurian fantasy, Classical fantasy (based on Greek and Roman myths), Shenmo (Gods and Demons), etc. Use for: fiction that is inspired by, or a retelling of, or that in some way draws from the characters, stories or themes of myth, legend, folklore, or fairy tales, for example, a story based on a popular fairy tale or myth or character from a classic work in a modern setting or a story based on a minor character’s perspective, or that takes a ‘what if’ approach or create a mashup of different genres, for example, fairy tale meets dystopian future, or mythology crossed with contemporary adventure story

Class here: Medieval, Dark Age, Arabian, Celtic, Gunpowder, Prehistoric, Wuxia fantasy. Use for: fantasy that incorporates fantastic elements, such as magic or supernatural beings, into recognisable historic settings, periods, cultures etc. Use with: PLACE 1* and/or TIME PERIOD 3* Qualifiers to indicate setting as appropriate
Zde zařaďte: ‚Temnou romanci‘, upírský romantický příběh atd.; zadejte podle potřeby také 5X
Use for: fantasy stories with darker and frightening themes, often incorporating elements of horror or that have a gloomy and threatening atmosphere or a sense of horror and dread

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Contemporary and urban fantasy
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: fantasy set in the present day or recognisably contemporary settings (according to the time period of its creator)

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Tradiční příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: pohádky, pověsti, mýty a legendy vyprávěné jako fiktivní příběh Zobrazit také YFHG

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Náboženská beletrie
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: Faith-inspired or inspirational stories. Use for: fiction that promotes a particular religious, spiritual or visionary message or viewpoint. Use with: 5PG* values from INTEREST 5* Qualifiers or YNR* codes, to indicate the religious tradition, as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Romance & milostné příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: stories that deal with all kinds of relationships with others; for stories where interpersonal relationships are the main theme; or explore the relationship of the main characters. Use with: YX* to give details of kinds of relationships as appropriate, for example, YXH for stories about relationships in peer groups Zobrazit také YXHB
Use for: stories where the main or primary topic or theme of the narrative is the friendship between different child or teenage main characters

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Romance and love stories
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: contemporary romance, romantic comedy, romantic drama, stories of first or young love, teenage romances, teenage love-triangles, lost love, unrequited love, etc. Use for: stories that are clearly of the romance genre and feature a romantic relationship as the core theme, that are specifically written for teenagers and deal with romance or love stories from a teenage point of view. Use with: YNX* codes as appropriate, with YFT and TIME PERIOD 3* qualifiers for Historical romance, with YFQ for comic romance, etc Zobrazit také YFHR

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Rodinné & domácí příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte s kódy z řady YXF* pro beletrii speciálně zaměřenou na otázky rodiny

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Příběhy o přírodě & zvířatech
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: YNN* codes to indicate what type of animal or nature story, for example YNNJ24 for Horse stories or YNN21 for stories about Dogs

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Humoristické příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Pokud je to možné, použijte po dalším kódu YF* označujícím žánr

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Sportovní příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: YNW* codes to indicate the sport in the story

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Školní příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: back to school, going to a new school, school life, stories principally taking place in and around school, etc. Use with: values from 5L* to indicate what school level as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Historická beletrie
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte pro současné romány odehrávající se v minulosti, tj. před rokem 1960

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Krátké povídky
Code.CodeNotes: Pokud je to možné, použijte po dalším kódu YF* označujícím žánr

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Veršované příběhy
Code.CodeNotes: Pokud je to možné, použijte po dalším kódu YF* označujícím žánr Zobrazit také YDP

Code.CodeDescription: Beletrie pro děti a mládež: Biografický román
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte pro vysoce fiktivní biografie nebo autobiografie skutečných lidí

Code.CodeDescription: Pro děti a mládež: Skutečné příběhy vyprávěné jako fikce
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: skutečné příběhy, např. o přežití, objevu, konfliktu atd., vyprávěné silně narativní formou, jako kdyby šlo o beletrii

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Special features and related items
Code.CodeNotes: Use all YFZ* codes with: other YF* code indicating genre or type. NB: YFZ* codes should not usually be the primary or main subject code

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Advent calendar stories
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: stories aimed at children or teenagers, usually in 24 or 25 chapters or stories, meant to be read, heard or seen as a countdown to Christmas through the Advent season. Use with: 5HPDA

Use for: genre fiction, usually published on a monthly basis, short, in clearly delineated lines and with a certain number published every month. Use with: other YF* code indicating genre or type. YFZR codes should never be the main subject code

Use for: short fiction for children or teenagers, usually driven primarily by dialogue and character, and generally accompanied by illustrations in manga/anime or similar styles. Use with: other YF* codes to indicate the genre

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Stories in translation
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: fiction in translation from another language. Use with: YF* codes to ensure classification is meaningful beyond the translation of the work itself. DO NOT USE: PLACE 1* or LANGUAGE 2* Qualifiers to describe the detail of the original language, this would be described elsewhere and not using Thema. You may still use a PLACE Qualifier if it is relevant to the plot or setting of the book. DO NOT USE: YFZT as the main or primary subject or the only code

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Stories Inspired by or adapted from other media
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: stories that were published as spin-offs or companions to pre-existing non-book media or merchandise, for example story books based on a popular film franchise, toy, an online game or a TV series. DO NOT USE: for titles that were subsequently made into films etc. Use with: other YF* code indicating genre or type. NB: YFZV codes should never be the main subject code

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage fiction: Game-related / LitRPG stories
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: Literary Role Playing Game, GameLit, RoLit. Use for: fiction that is structured like a videogame, or features the same kind of challenges as would be found in a game, or is about or set in a videogame. Use with: other YF* codes as appropriate

Use for: companion works to popular children’s or teenage fiction series or titles, typically uncritical, such as an atlas of a mythical world, a compendium of characters, a guide to the series, etc. Use with: other Y* codes or on its own as appropriate

Použijte kódy YN*pro všechny obecné zájmové materiály, které nejsou zahrnuty jinde a které nejsou určeny speciálně pro školní použití . Použijte samotné kódy YN* pro literaturu faktu nebo, podle potřeby, po příslušném kódu YF* pro beletrii zabývající se konkrétními náměty. Vedle kódů YN* zadejte náležitý kvalifikátor čtenářského věku / úrovně 5A* tam, kde je potřeba, a podle potřeby další kvalifikátor.

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Umění & umělci
Code.CodeNotes: Zadejte podle potřeby kvalifikátory STYLU

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Biografie & autobiografie
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: both individual biographies and works that have multiple biographies of different people, titles about heroes or heroines, inspirational figures, famous and everyday people, diaries or journals of individuals. Use with: other YN* codes for particular genres of biography

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Hudba
Code.CodeNotes: Zadejte podle potřeby kvalifikátory STYLU

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Musical instruments
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: musical instruction, learning to play the piano, the recorder, the guitar, musical scores, etc. Use with: AVR* codes to indicate specific instruments if more detail is appropriate. NB: if mixing Y* codes with AVR* codes, the Y* code MUST be designated as the Main Subject and sent with a 5A* qualifier
Class here: song scores, sing along, learning to sing. Use with: STYLE 6* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Drama & vystupování
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: circus, acting techniques, stagecraft, theatre, auditions, etc. Use with: STYLE 6* Qualifiers as appropriate, or with YNB for biographies of performers

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Tanec, balet
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: learning to dance. Use with: STYLE 6* Qualifiers as appropriate, or with YNB for biographies of dancers or dance groups

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Herní scénáře
Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Televize & film
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: titles about making of a film, TV, series, streaming, digital filmmaking, animation, radio, podcasting, etc. Use with: STYLE 6* Qualifiers as appropriate, or with YNB for biographies of actors, TV, film or video stars, personalities or celebrities

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Všeobecné znalosti & vědomostní hry
Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Knihovny, muzea, školy
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: titles about libraries, museums, schools, using and finding information, guides to using information resources, etc. Use for: informative books about museums, galleries, libraries other cultural centres, and their content

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Historie & minulost
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte YNB pro biografie konkrétních lidí Zobrazit také YNB YPJH

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Dobrodružství & psanci
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: piráti, hledači pokladů Zobrazit také YNB

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Objevy & průzkumy
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: objevy nových kontinentů, vnitrozemí, planet atd. Zobrazit také YNB

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Životy dětí v minulosti
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: PLACE 1* and TIME PERIOD 3* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Válčení, bitvy, ozbrojené síly
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: soldiers, gladiators, warriors, wars, uniforms, military vehicles. Use with: other YN* codes and PLACE 1* and TIME PERIOD 3* Qualifiers as appropriate Zobrazit také YXZW

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Castles and knights
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: medieval warfare

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Práce & společnost
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: business, the world of work, working or different jobs, specific professions, daily life, everyday occurrences, first jobs, aspects of society or contemporary culture, cultural phenomenon, entrepreneurs, everyday happenings, etc. Use with: YNH for history titles, YXZ* for social issues

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Politika
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: titles about politicians, politics, political activity, political institutions, government, human rights, political debates, geopolitics explain different political concepts, ideologies, political strategies, political parties or movements, single issues politics, to young people. Use with: YNB and YNH, as appropriate, for biographies of political figures or history titles. NB: YNKA may be used with JP* codes to give extra detail if there is no specific Y* code or qualifier but if mixing YNKA with JP* codes, a Y* code MUST be designated as the Main Subject and sent with a 5A* code

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Zákony, policie & zločin
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works that look at topics around crime, legal matter, law enforcement or are about those that work in these roles, police officers, judges, lawyers, etc or look at criminals or criminality. Use with: YNB for biographies of people in this domain or YNH for history titles

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Medical and emergency services
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: doctors, nurses, health workers, carers, ambulances, paramedics, fire and rescue services, lifeboat services, mountain rescue, a visit to the hospital, the doctor, the dentist, the fire station, etc. Use for: works about the medical, health care and emergency sectors or the people who work in these sectors. Use with: YNB for biographies of people in this domain

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Literatura, knihy & spisovatelé
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: YNB for biographies of writers

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Místa & lidé
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: travel titles or travel guides for young people. Use with: PLACE 1* or INTEREST 5P* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Země, kultury & národní identita
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: národní symboly, památníky, oblečení atd.

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Celebrations, holidays, festivals and special events
Code.CodeNotes: Use with: values from 5H* INTEREST Qualifiers as appropriate, also use with YNR* codes as appropriate Zobrazit také YNR* 5H*

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Dívky & ženy
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte pro knihy, kde dívčí léta / dospělost ženy jsou ústředním tématem

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Chlapci & muži
Code.CodeNotes: Použijte pro knihy, kde chlapecká léta / dospělost muže jsou ústředním tématem

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Velkoměstský & městský život
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: suburbs, inner cities, small towns, urban and suburban life, streets, houses, neighbourhoods. Use for: books about life in urban environments or works about particular cities or towns. Use with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers especially if about a named city which has a PLACE 1* code

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Venkovský & farmářský život
Children’s / Teenage general interest: Home and daily life
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: my home, house, flat, apartment, the place I live, moving house, moving to a new place, everyday domestic life, etc. Use for: works around topics or themes of home life, everyday activities or things in a domestic situation, talking about homes or changing homes or places

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Královské rodiny
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: royalty, empresses, emperors. Use for: titles about royals or featuring a royal character. Use with: with YNB for biographies, or YNH for history and PLACE 1* and/or TIME PERIOD 3* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Příroda, zvířata, svět přírody
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: the life sciences (non-educational), evolution, ecology, natural history, nature writing, the living world, life cycles

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Dinosauři & prehistorický svět
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: woolly mammoths, fossils, prehistoric life, extinct megafauna, palaeontology, prehistoric mammals, ice age world. Use with: TIME PERIOD 3* Qualifiers as appropriate

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Divoká zvířata & biotopy (jejich přirozené prostředí)
Code.CodeNotes: Zobrazit také YXZG

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Divoká zvířata & biotopy: Oceány & moře
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: seashore, coasts, beaches, etc

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Divoká zvířata & biotopy: Džungle & tropické lesy
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: deštné pralesy

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Divoká zvířata & biotopy: Pouště
Children’s / Teenage general interest: Wildlife and habitats: Woodlands and forests
Children’s / Teenage general interest: Wildlife and habitats: Savannas and grasslands
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: prairies, meadows, steppes

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Divoká zvířata & biotopy: Led, sníh & tundra
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: Biotopy: polární oblasti a vysoké hory

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Ekosystémy
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: díla o veškerých ekosystémech Zobrazit také YXZG

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Sounds of nature and the natural world
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: works about or featuring sounds from the natural world, such as bird songs, animal sounds, animal noises, how animals communicate, sounds of the seas, of the forests, weather sounds, etc. Use with: other YNN* codes for more precise details, such as YNNK for bird songs, YNNJ14 for whale song

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Hospodářská zvířata
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: general works that include multiple farm animals or for farm animals that do not have their own code

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Domácí mazlíčci & péče o ně
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: feeding and general care of domestic animals and pets, cooking and preparing food for pets or domesticated creatures, general guidance for nutrition, health, welfare and care of pets

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Domácí mazlíčci & péče o ně: psi
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: puppies, training a dog Zobrazit také YNNJ21

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Domácí mazlíčci & péče o ně: kočky
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: kittens Zobrazit také YNNJ22

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Domácí mazlíčci & péče o ně: králíci & hlodavci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: mice, hamsters, guinea pigs, gerbils, rats etc, as pets Zobrazit také YNNJ31

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Domácí mazlíčci & péče o ně: koně & poníci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: taking care of your pony or horse, grooming, feeding and exercising a horse Zobrazit také YNNJ24

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Pets and pet care: Birds
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: parrots, canaries, budgerigars etc as pets

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Savci
Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Vodní & mořští savci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: hippopotamus, otters, beavers, seals, walruses. Use for: mammals that live most of the time in water Zobrazit také YNNS

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Whales, dolphins and porpoises
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: mammals that live permanently in water

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Velká suchozemská zvířata
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: camels, elephants, giraffes, rhinoceros, llamas, etc. Use for: any work featuring or about large mammals that does not have its own code or note

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Psi & vlci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: hyenas, foxes etc. Use for: any work featuring or about any type of dog (canid), that is not specifically about pet care Zobrazit také YNNH1

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Kočky
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: velké kočky Zobrazit také YNNH2

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Medvědi
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: giant pandas

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Poníci & koně
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: donkeys, asses, zebras. Use with: YF* codes for stories or fiction about horses, with YNW* for equestrian sports Zobrazit také YNNH4

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Krávy & dobytek
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: buffalo, bison, yaks

Code.CodeDescription: Children’s / Teenage general interest: Pigs, hogs and boars
Children’s / Teenage general interest: Sheep and goats
Children’s / Teenage general interest: Deer, moose, reindeers
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: elk, caribou, antelope

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Lidoopi & opice
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: gorillas, chimpanzees, orangutans, gibbons

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Malá suchozemská zvířata
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: bats, hedgehogs, racoons, etc. Use for: any work featuring or about small mammals that does not have its own code or note

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Hlodavci & králíci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: mice, rats, squirrels, hares, porcupines, capybaras, etc, not as pets Zobrazit také YNNH3

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Vačnatci, ptakořitní & ježurovití
Code.CodeNotes: Zde zařaďte: klokani, koaly

Code.CodeDescription: Obecné zájmy dětí a mládeže: Ptáci
Code.CodeNotes: Class here: owls, chicks, herons, cranes, penguins, parrots, toucans, ducks, geese, turkeys, swans, vultures, flamingos, ostriches, emus, puffins, eagles, etc

Use PLACE 1* Qualifier codes WITH appropriate subject codes for: indicating the geographical scope and applicability of the content, such as the location of a travel guide, the setting of a novel, the jurisdiction to which laws apply, the history of a particular place, the peoples, arts, traditions, or culture of a particular geographical location, etc. Where options exist, e.g. terms representing actual, historical, cultural, administrative, or geophysical entities, use the expression that best suits the content. Where no code exists for a specific location, use the nearest most appropriate broader code that includes it. DO NOT USE: to indicate any geographical aspect that is not to do with the content or subject of a book (e.g. place of publication, market availability, nationality of author – this is described in other metadata, etc). National extensions (i.e. 1*-xx- format codes, where ‘xx’ indicates a country code) can be assigned by any user, and are not exclusive to users in the indicated country. This section is not intended as an exhaustive gazetteer of all places but a list of commonly used locations in the global book supply chain. Nepoužívejte “5” na jednotlivé knihy, ale vyberte podle potřeby kvalifikátory ze sekce 5*

Use all 5A* age codes for: defining the Y* or X* codes – 5A* age numbers are used instead of named codes, such as juvenile, middle grade, young adult, as these have different meanings in different countries or languages. Select one 5A* code indicating a general guideline starting or base interest age of the content in any works aimed primarily at children or teenagers. All Y* codes (except YP* which use 4* codes) MUST be accompanied by one 5A* qualifier code to give guidance of interest age, for example: book content for 9 to 12 age group, should use 5AK; content of interest to teenagers should use 5AP or 5AQ; content for older teenagers and young adults should use 5AS, 5AT or 5AU as appropriate. 5AR, 5AX and 5AZ can be used with any relevant subject code. All 5A* codes can be used with X* subject codes if the Comic book is aimed at children or teenagers. DO NOT USE: 5A itself – always use 5A* codes. NB: Greater detail of age range, reading age, interest age etc would be communicated in other metadata

This could include content specifically adapted for people with, for example, dyslexia and other reading or learning disabilities, cognitive impairments or disorders, memory disorders, dementia or Alzheimer’s, visual or other sensory impairments, etc. Use with: 5PM* Qualifiers as appropriate

Use all 5H* codes for: indicating that the content of a work is largely about or relates to the holiday, event or season, for example a book featuring a Christmas story would use 5HPD or a book about birthdays for children would use 5HKA, a romance story that is all about summer could use 5HRB. DO NOT USE: to indicate a targeted audience for marketing purposes, the content should be primarily about this stage of life or age group

Use for: material that has major or principal themes relating to, or is primarily about adulthood or being an adult

Use with: FR* for ‘New Adult Romance’ or ‘College Romance’, FP for ‘New Adult Erotica’, FM* for ‘New Adult Fantasy’, etc. when the main themes of a novel are specifically related to this stage of life and use with non-fiction codes for studies, themes or content about this passage from teenager to adult

Code.CodeDescription: Relating to migrant groups / diaspora communities or peoples
Code.CodeNotes: Use for: material where the major or principal themes, topics or storylines relate to, (historical and recent) groups of people or persons who have migrated or were exiled or displaced from one part of the world to another; or are part of a diaspora community and who maintain a strong and distinct identity associated with another geographical or cultural area within their present place of residence. Use all 5PBC* codes with: PLACE 1* Qualifiers as appropriate, to indicate the geographical area that is the subject of the work, usually where that group is now, for example, a title about Syrian migrant communities in Sweden, use with 1DNS, or a title about Guatemalan migrant workers in Mexico, use with 1KLCM or a study of German exiled writers of the mid-twentieth century, in the USA, use with 1KBB Zobrazit také 5PBD
